- "employed" refers to individuals who are currently working and receiving regular income;
- "average weekly earnings" is the mean amount of money earned per week by employed individuals;
- "region_name" and "gender_name" are used to categorize the results, providing a detailed view of earnings across different regions and genders.

sql:
SELECT AVG(weekly_earnings) AS average_weekly_earnings
FROM individuals
WHERE employment_status = 'employed';

